Some youths in the Northcentral region have called on a former President of the Senate, Dr Bukola Saraki to contest the presidency in 2023. They argued that the former governor of Kwara State has what it takes to unite the country and grow the economy. National Coordinator, Coalition of Saraki Advocates (COSA), Amb. Saidu Usman and Secretary General, Amb. Ibrahim Jeje, said this at the inauguration of new executives for the group.   Obi Cubana offers Lagos hawker university scholarship,…     IPOB’s peculiar hyperbole     Why governors are not Chief Security Officers, by lawyer   In a statement in Abuja on Saturday, the coalition said it would continue to canvas for more members and keep enlightening people on the antecedents of Saraki and his exemplary leadership style. Speaking of the former Senate President, the statement read: “Saraki, a man in his mid fifties is no doubt the person that would be mostly acceptable to the northern and southern elites and the people in general, considering his laudable achievements as the President of 8th Senate of Federal Republic of Nigeria. - Advertisement - “…To this end in our own genuine view of nation building, a man of good will in person of Dr. Abubakar Bukola Saraki should be given the chance, as his pedigree and records in national politics speaks volumes.”